summary: This is an automatic out-of-office email reply from an Assistant United States Attorney (AUSA) involved in the Epstein case, indicating they were on vacation until August 12, 2019, and directing urgent matters to other AUSAs on the case.
keyFacts: An Assistant United States Attorney (AUSA) working on the Epstein case was on vacation on August 10, 2019.
The email indicates there were multiple AUSAs assigned to the case at that time.
The document is an automatic reply email, showing routine office communication during the investigation/prosecution.
